{"title_page": "Mathew Thomas", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actor}}\n{{BLP sources|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Mathew Thomas\n| image         = \n| caption       =\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|2002|10|16|df=yes}}\n| birth_place   = [[Thiruvamkulam]], Kerala, India\n| occupation    = Actor\n| yearsactive   = 2019\u2013present\n| awards        = \n}}\n\n'''Mathew Thomas''' (born 16 October 2002) is an Indian actor who appears in [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam films]]. He made his acting debut in 2019 with ''[[Kumbalangi Nights]]'' at age 16, playing one of the four siblings in the film.\n\n==Early life==\nMathew Thomas was born 16 October 2002 in [[Thiruvamkulam]], [[Ernakulam district]] of [[Kerala]], India. His father, Biju John Thuruthiyil, works as a Civil Engineer and his mother, Susan is a senior secondary school teacher in Mathematics. Mathew has an elder brother, John Thomas. Mathew did his play schooling at Hagia Sophia Public School Ernakulam. He also studied in Indian School, Manama, Bahrain for few years while his parents were employed there temporarily. Upon return, he joined Gregorian Public School Mardu Eranakulam from where he was auditioned for his first movie [[Kumbalangi Nights]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Luck bu Accident |url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/movies/interview/2019/08/06/mathew-thomas-kumbalangi-actor.html |accessdate=16 March 2020 |date=16 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nMathew played the role of Franky Napolean, one of the 4 orphaned siblings in the lead role, alongside [[Soubin Shahir]], [[Shane Nigam]], [[Sreenath Bhasi]], [[Anna Ben]], [[Fahadh Faasil]] and [[Grace Antony]]. Franky is a district level football player, who also keeps their home, up and running, because, all his siblings are either drunk or always out with their friends. \n\nMathew was auditioned from his school<ref>{{cite news |title=New kid on the block |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/new-kid-on-the-block-mathew-thomas-is-relishing-the-sweet-success-of-malayalam-film-thanneermathan-dinangal/article28846886.ece |accessdate=10 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref> <ref>{{cite news |title=The Fourth Brother of Kumbalangi |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/110219/the-fourth-brother-of-kumbalangi.html |accessdate=10 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref> and had to learn several skills like swimming in the deep, casting a net, play football, row a boat etc. Since it was his debut, he spent 6 months at the location of the movie, undergoing several training sessions with the experienced, coming home only once or twice a month. The movie was a great success and Mathew's performance was very well received considering that it was his debut movie.\n\nMathew's soon cast into his second film [[Thanneer Mathan Dinangal]], as a high-school student Jaison. The third movie Mathew appears in is [[Midhun Manuel Thomas]]'s [[Anjaam Pathiraa]] where he plays the younger days of the antagonist, Dr. Benjamin Louis.\n\n== Filmography ==\n=== As an actor ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+Key\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\"| {{dagger|alt=Films that have not yet been released}}\n| Denotes films that have not yet been released\n|}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Director\n! Notes\n! Ref.\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Kumbalangi Nights]]''\n| Franky Napoleon\n| Madhu C. Narayanan\n| At age of 16.\n| <ref>{{cite news |title=My character in Kumbalangi Nights isn't very different from me|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/my-character-in-kumbalangi-nights-isnt-very-different-from-me/articleshow/67827686.cms |accessdate=10 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[Thanneer Mathan Dinangal]]''\n| Jaison\n| Girish A. D.\n|\n| <ref>{{cite news |title=Success |url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/190819/sweet-success.html |accessdate=10 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[Anjaam Pathiraa]]''\n| Benjamin Louis\n| [[Midhun Manuel Thomas]]\n|\n| <ref>{{cite news |title=The timid guy who later became a psycho |url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/midhun-manuel-thomas-anjaam-pathiraa-is-an-investigative-thriller/article30459237.ece |accessdate=10 March 2020 |date=10 March 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\" | ''One''{{dagger}}\n| \n| Santhosh Viswanath\n| Post-production\n| <ref>{{cite news |title=Mammootty to soon begin shooting for 'One' |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/mammootty-to-soon-begin-shooting-for-one/articleshow/71690258.cms| accessdate=15 March 2020 |website=Times Of India}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=The first look\n|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/131119/the-first-look.html| accessdate=15 March 2020 |website=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2020\n| style=\"background:#ffc;\" | [[Draft:Operation Java|''Operation Java'']]\n| \n| Tharun Moorthy\n| Pre-production\n| <ref>{{cite news |title=It's pack up time for team Operation Java |url= https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/movies/news/its-pack-up-time-for-team-operation-java/articleshow/74439246.cms | accessdate=15 March 2020 |website=Deccan Chronicle}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Awards==\n* 2020 \u2013 [[Asianet Film Awards]] for Best Star Pair of the Year \u2013 [[Thanneer Mathan Dinangal]] (shared with [[Anaswara Rajan]])<ref>{{cite news |title=Asianet Film Awards announced 2020; Here's the complete list of winners! |url=http://onlookersmedia.in/latestnews/asianet-film-awards-announced-2020-heres-complete-list-winners/ |accessdate=13 March 2020 |date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n* 2020 \u2013 [[Vanitha Film Awards]] for Best Newcomer Actor of the Year \u2013 [[Thanneer Mathan Dinangal]] and [[Kumbalangi Nights]] <ref>{{cite news |title=Vanitha Film Awards 2020 |url=https://english.