{"title_page": "Harem Girl", "text_new": "{{Infobox film\n| name           = Harem Girl\n| image          = Harem Girl poster.jpg\n| alt            = \n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Edward Bernds]]\n| producer       = [[Wallace MacDonald]]\n| screenplay     = Edward Bernds<br>[[Elwood Ullman]]\n| story          = Edward Bernds \n| starring       = [[Joan Davis]]<br>[[Peggie Castle]]<br>Arthur Blake<br>[[Paul Marion (actor)|Paul Marion]]<br>[[Donald Randolph]]<br>[[Henry Brandon (actor)|Henry Brandon]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = [[Lester White]] \n| editing        = [[Richard Fantl]]\n| studio         = [[Columbia Pictures]]\n| distributor    = Columbia Pictures\n| released       = {{Film date|1952|1|21}}\n| runtime        = 71 minutes\n| country        = United States\n| language       = English\n| budget         = \n| gross          = \n}}\n\n'''''Harem Girl''''' is a 1952 American [[comedy film]] directed by [[Edward Bernds]] and written by Edward Bernds and [[Elwood Ullman]]. The film stars [[Joan Davis]], [[Peggie Castle]], Arthur Blake, [[Paul Marion (actor)|Paul Marion]], [[Donald Randolph]] and [[Henry Brandon (actor)|Henry Brandon]]. The film was released on January 21, 1952, by [[Columbia Pictures]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/27405/Harem-Girl/ |title=Harem Girl (1952) - Overview |publisher=TCM.com |date= |accessdate=2019-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Hal Erickson |url=https://www.allmovie.com/movie/harem-girl-v94356 |title=Harem Girl (1952) - Edward Bernds |publisher=AllMovie |date= |accessdate=2019-05-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://catalog.afi.com/Film/50503-HAREM-GIRL |title=Harem Girl |publisher=Catalog.afi.com |date= |accessdate=2019-05-26}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n{{no plot|date=May 2019}}\n\n==Cast==          \n* [[Joan Davis]] as Susie Perkins\n* [[Peggie Castle]] as Princess Shareen\n* Arthur Blake as Abdul Nassib\n* [[Paul Marion (actor)|Paul Marion]] as Majeed\n* [[